current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Relational Databases
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Relational databases are a powerful tool used throughout the industry. Learn the basics of SQL and how to connect your Python code to a relational database.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Algorithms
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This class will give you an introduction to the design and analysis of algorithms, enabling you to analyze networks and discover how individuals are connected.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Model Building and Validation
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This course will teach you how to start from scratch in understanding and paying attention to what is important in the data and how to answer questions about data

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Differential Equations in Action
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Write Python code to find numerical solutions to systems of differential equations. The models you create will fight wildfires, bring spaceships back to earth, and more!

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Designing RESTful APIs
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Build and secure a web server with a RESTful Developer-Friendly API that developers will love to use.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Make Your Own 2048
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Ten minutes into this class you'll make your own completely personalized version of the insanely addictive game 2048. Even if you've never coded before. Pretty cool, no?

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Linux Command Line Basics
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: An introduction to the Linux command line interface.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: OMSCS Student Orientation
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: In this OMS Orientation, we cover several things you will need to know to be a successful OMS student.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Data Structures & Algorithms in Python
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn the skills technical interviewers expect you to know—efficiency, common algorithms, manipulating popular data structures, and how to explain a solution.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Time Series Forecasting
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn the fundamentals of time series forecasting and develop proficiency in ETS and ARIMA models, two the most commonly used models in forecasting.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Asynchronous JavaScript Requests
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This course covers everything you need to know to asynchronously request data in your web apps. You'll dive into async requests by using the XHR object, jQuery's .ajax method, and the Fetch API.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Machine Learning for Trading
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Implement machine learning based strategies to make trading decisions using real-world data.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: JavaScript Basics
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn JavaScript syntax and coding conventions that web developers use to create interactive and dynamic websites while you create an online résumé for your portfolio.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Educational Technology
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This class is an an introductory course about educational technology offered as CS6460 at Georgia Tech where it is a part of the Online Masters Degree (OMS).

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Machine Learning
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This class will teach you the end-to-end process of investigating data through a machine learning lens, and you'll apply what you've learned to a real-world data set.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Reinforcement Learning
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Study machine learning at a deeper level and become a participant in the reinforcement learning research community.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Learn Swift Programming Syntax
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This course focuses on the syntax of the Swift programming language. By the end of the course, you'll be able to apply Swift essentials to building iOS apps.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Data Analysis
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Explore a variety of datasets, posing and answering your own questions about each. You'll be using the Python libraries NumPy, Pandas, and Matplotlib.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Artificial Intelligence
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This course will introduce you to the basics of AI. Topics include machine learning, probabilistic reasoning, robotics, computer vision, and natural language processing.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Programming Foundations with Python
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Introductory programming class to learn Object-Oriented Programming, a must-have technique to reuse and share code easily. Learn by making projects that spread happiness!

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to HTML and CSS
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn how to convert digital design mockups into static web pages and how to build a responsive portfolio site to showcase your work.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: HTML5 Game Development
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn how to build high-performance web games with HTML5. We'll port industry-standard development techniques to the web and use them to create a game.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Passwordless Login Solutions for iOS
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: In this course you'll implement Account Kit and Facebook Login side by side in a sample app, test our login flow on a series of common use cases, and wrap things up with an introduction to Facebook’s

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Applied Cryptography
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Cryptography is present in everyday life, from paying with a credit card to using the telephone.  Learn all about making and breaking puzzles in computing.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Inferential Statistics
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Intro to Inferential Statistics will teach you how to test your hypotheses and begin to make predictions based on statistical results drawn from data!

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Introduction to Operating Systems
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Introduction to Operating Systems teaches the basic operating system abstractions, mechanisms, and their implementations.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Developing Android Apps
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Build a cloud-connected Android app, and learn the tools, principles, and best practices of mobile and Android development that you'll apply to your own projects.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to the Design of Everyday Things
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This course will provide you with the insight to start recognizing the role of design in today’s world, and to start making better design decisions in your own life.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Physics
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Go to the places where big physics discoveries were made in the past and make them yourself. You’ll visit Italy, the Netherlands, and the UK as you learn basic physics.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Programming Languages
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This course is an introduction to the fundamentals of programming languages. Concepts include how to specify and process valid strings, sentences and program structures.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Descriptive Statistics
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Intro to Descriptive Statistics will teach you the basic concepts of statistics that can be used to extract information from data.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Mobile Web Development
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: In this course, you'll learn how to build great mobile web experiences. We'll cover performance issues on mobile, and how to make use of mobile sensors.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Data Science
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: What does a data scientist do? In this course, we will survey the main topics in data science so you can understand the skills that are needed to become a data scientist!

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: JavaScript Design Patterns
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn the importance of code organization and how to implement it with either vanilla JavaScript or an organizational library or framework.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Linear Algebra Refresher Course
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn linear algebra by doing: you will code your own library of linear algebra functions!

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Swift for Beginners
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: This course offers an entry into the world of coding and an introduction to Apple’s Swift programming language. Writing in Swift, students are introduced to basic programming concepts.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Theoretical Computer Science
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn the basic concepts in theoretical computer science. Discover what they imply for solving tough computational challenges.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Intro to Java Programming
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn essential computer science and object-oriented programming concepts in this introductory Java course.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Website Performance Optimization
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn how browsers convert HTML, CSS and JavaScript into websites while you experiment with Chrome Developer Tools to measure and optimize website speed!

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Software Testing
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Learn how to catch bugs and break software as you discover different testing methods that will help you build better software.

current_nanodegrees_and_courses.title: Software Development Process
current_nanodegrees_and_courses.summary: Software Development Processes explores requirements engineering, architecture and design, testing, and software quality in general.
